    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-08-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="62" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Pacheco</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-08-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 13,
                            1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Wharton acknowledges Mr. Pacheco’s telegram of the 10th instant and calls
                        his attention to Department’s telegram of the same date. He is <pb facs="0175" n="69" xml:id="pg_69"/> instructed to protest against any
                        arbitrary actions by the authorities of Salvador toward the steamship <hi rend="italic">City of Panama</hi>, even if vessel has been seized, which
                        would not affect instructions previously sent him. A full report of the
                        facts is asked for.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
